.SH NAME
Net::Nostr::Deletion \- NIP\-09 event deletion requests
.SH SYNOPSIS
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
.Vb 1
\&    use Net::Nostr::Deletion;
\&
\&    # Create a deletion request
\&    my $del = Net::Nostr::Deletion\->new(reason => \*(Aqposted by accident\*(Aq);
\&    $del\->add_event($event_id, kind => 1);
\&    $del\->add_event($other_id, kind => 1);
\&    $del\->add_address("30023:$pubkey:my\-article", kind => 30023);
\&    $del\->add_address("10000:$pubkey:", kind => 10000);  # replaceable
\&
\&    my $event = $del\->to_event(pubkey => $my_pubkey);
\&    $key\->sign_event($event);
\&    $client\->publish($event);
\&
\&    # Parse a received deletion request
\&    my $del = Net::Nostr::Deletion\->from_event($event);
\&    say $del\->reason;
\&    say join \*(Aq, \*(Aq, @{$del\->event_ids};
\&
\&    # Check if a deletion applies to a specific event
\&    if ($del\->applies_to($target_event, $deletion_event\->pubkey)) {
\&        # hide or delete the target event
\&    }
.Ve
.SH DESCRIPTION
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
Implements NIP\-09 event deletion requests. A deletion request is a kind 5
event containing \f(CW\*(C`e\*(C'\fR and/or \f(CW\*(C`a\*(C'\fR tags referencing events to be deleted,
and \f(CW\*(C`k\*(C'\fR tags indicating the kinds of those events.
.PP
Deletion requests are just requests \- relays and clients SHOULD honor them
but there is no guarantee that events will be deleted from all relays.
.SH CONSTRUCTOR
.IX Header "CONSTRUCTOR"
.SS new
.IX Subsection "new"
.Vb 2
\&    my $del = Net::Nostr::Deletion\->new;
\&    my $del = Net::Nostr::Deletion\->new(reason => \*(Aqposted by accident\*(Aq);
.Ve
.PP
Creates an empty deletion request. \f(CW\*(C`reason\*(C'\fR is optional and becomes the
event\*(Aqs \f(CW\*(C`content\*(C'\fR field. Croaks on unknown arguments.
.SS from_event
.IX Subsection "from_event"
.Vb 1
\&    my $del = Net::Nostr::Deletion\->from_event($event);
.Ve
.PP
Parses a kind 5 event into a Deletion object. Tags with fewer than
two elements are silently skipped. Croaks if the event is not kind 5.
.PP
.Vb 4
\&    my $del = Net::Nostr::Deletion\->from_event($event);
\&    for my $id (@{$del\->event_ids}) {
\&        say "delete: $id";
\&    }
.Ve
.SH METHODS
.IX Header "METHODS"
.SS add_event
.IX Subsection "add_event"
.Vb 1
\&    $del\->add_event($event_id, kind => 1);
.Ve
.PP
Adds an event ID to the deletion request. \f(CW\*(C`kind\*(C'\fR is required and will
be included as a \f(CW\*(C`k\*(C'\fR tag. Returns \f(CW$self\fR for chaining.
.PP
.Vb 2
\&    $del\->add_event($id1, kind => 1)
\&        \->add_event($id2, kind => 1);
.Ve
.SS add_address
.IX Subsection "add_address"
.Vb 2
\&    $del\->add_address("30023:$pubkey:my\-article", kind => 30023);
\&    $del\->add_address("10000:$pubkey:", kind => 10000);  # replaceable
.Ve
.PP
Adds an event coordinate (\f(CW\*(C`a\*(C'\fR tag) to the deletion request. The coordinate
may be addressable (\f(CW\*(C`kind:pubkey:d_tag\*(C'\fR) or replaceable (\f(CW\*(C`kind:pubkey:\*(C'\fR
with empty d_tag). \f(CW\*(C`kind\*(C'\fR is required. Returns \f(CW$self\fR for chaining.
.SS event_ids
.IX Subsection "event_ids"
.Vb 1
\&    my $ids = $del\->event_ids;  # arrayref
.Ve
.PP
Returns the list of event IDs referenced by \f(CW\*(C`e\*(C'\fR tags.
.SS addresses
.IX Subsection "addresses"
.Vb 1
\&    my $addrs = $del\->addresses;  # arrayref
.Ve
.PP
Returns the list of event coordinates referenced by \f(CW\*(C`a\*(C'\fR tags (both
addressable and replaceable).
.SS reason
.IX Subsection "reason"
.Vb 1
\&    my $reason = $del\->reason;
.Ve
.PP
Returns the deletion reason (the event\*(Aqs \f(CW\*(C`content\*(C'\fR), or empty string.
.SS to_event
.IX Subsection "to_event"
.Vb 2
\&    my $event = $del\->to_event(pubkey => $pubkey_hex);
\&    my $event = $del\->to_event(pubkey => $pubkey_hex, created_at => time());
.Ve
.PP
Creates a kind 5 Net::Nostr::Event from the deletion request. Extra
arguments are passed through to the Event constructor.
.PP
.Vb 2
\&    my $event = $del\->to_event(pubkey => $key\->pubkey_hex);
\&    $key\->sign_event($event);
.Ve
.SS applies_to
.IX Subsection "applies_to"
.Vb 1
\&    my $bool = $del\->applies_to($target_event, $deletion_pubkey);
.Ve
.PP
Returns true if this deletion request applies to the given event.
Checks that:
.IP \(bu 4
The target event\*(Aqs pubkey matches the deletion request\*(Aqs pubkey
.IP \(bu 4
The target event\*(Aqs ID is referenced by an \f(CW\*(C`e\*(C'\fR tag, or its
addressable coordinate (\f(CW\*(C`kind:pubkey:d_tag\*(C'\fR) or replaceable coordinate
(\f(CW\*(C`kind:pubkey:\*(C'\fR) is referenced by an \f(CW\*(C`a\*(C'\fR tag
.PP
.Vb 3
\&    if ($del\->applies_to($event, $del_event\->pubkey)) {
\&        # event should be hidden/deleted
\&    }
.Ve
